items.name: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Stone Ocean
items.description:
Watching my second Anime ever "JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Stone Ocean" (The first was "One punch man"). Enjoying it a lot, so obviously fine-tuned a Stable-Diffusion model upon its images (After trying with hypernetwork a few times but failed, I chose full finetuning).

This is a full fine-tuning upon this blip-captioned dataset and there is no specific trigger word. You can try out some prompts online using the Inference Widget on Huggingface.

For some reason, limbs do not come out so well.

items.name: Princess Zelda LoRA
items.description:
Princess Zelda LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

This one turned out better then expected. I learned a couple of things and I may even retrain some of my early loras. Use it at around 0.5 weight.

Activation words are princess zelda and game titles (no underscores), which I'm not gonna list, as you can see them from the example prompts. It tends to lean a bit towards BoTW, but it's very flexible and allows for most Zelda versions. I used CLIP skip and AbyssOrangeMix2_nsfw for all the examples. And yes, this can do nsfw pics.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

items.name: Jennifer Aniston TI
items.description:
A few weeks ago (which in rapid SD time... is a long time ago), I raised a fuss on a few Checkpoint/Dreambooth models built of images of a single person, pointing out that TIs were better and significantly smaller. Feedback was mixed, and the #1 complaint was "TI's don't look as good" I offered to train a TI on the same images used. @malcolmrey was kind enough to take me up on the offer, and posted his training images for a few of the celebs he'd done. I finally got around to doing the comparison, and as I expected, the TIs looked better, IMHO. This is so people can compare on their own...

TIs do have some flaws about using the person in ways not trained (there are ways around this, including better training images). I didn't attempt to do this for this experiment, so asking for Jen riding a bicycle might yield her standing around instead. That's fixable, but not done in this case. (You can often cheat by asking for things like "A woman who looks like Jen, riding a bicycle" and other 'indirect' methods, but really it's better to just train less 'tight' TIs.)


So I posted this to the Civitai Discord, and asked people to guess which was which: Identify Mystery 1,2,3,4 with Stock 1.5 Jennifer, CKPT sks (the CKPT @malcolmrey posted), my TI-1000 steps and my TI-3500 steps

(answer is below... make your guesses first)

I also did a 2.x TI, which I'll include a few samples of as well...

I've uploaded a very big pile of other steps for both 15 and 2.x (as embedded pngs), to the 2.x-4500, as 'training data' (the actual training data is on Malcolm's CKPT upload) for those who want to try a bunch out and see how the TI changes over training... OR if one of them is better than the 4 I specifically pulled out here to add one by one...

Drop any of the pngs into your embedding folder, and they work just like .pt files otherwise.

Thanks to Malcolm and also to @justmaier for his support. Shout outs to all of the crew on the Discord too. Also to ALL of the amazing TI creators who have started posting TIs since my initial rant/complaints. TIs have proven themselves.

(the order, BTW, is 1000, Stock1.5, 3500, and Malcolm's CKPT - same (1 randomly picked) seed, same steps, CFG and TI changed, that's all)

items.name: Embroidery Style
items.description:
this model was trained with almost 400 images of the embroidery works of "Bordando Personajes Argentina".

the model specializes more in generating anime embroidery but can be quite versatile if you experiment enough.

to force the style you must use the prompt embroidery by embarg.

I have not achieved good results with img2img. more experimentation is needed.

training was done in 3000 steps with a learning rate 2e-6.

The text encoder was not trained. More than 6000 regularization images from the datasets waifu-regularization-3.3k and husbando-regularization-3.5k were used.

the base model was the SD 2.1 with 768 x 768 images.

all training was done on Google Colab free with a Tesla T4 and took about 1 hour.

the notebook used was the one from TheLastBen.

Typical negative prompts:

Disfigured, bad art, amateur, poorly drawn, ugly, flat, deformed, poorly drawn, extra limbs, close up, b&w, weird colors, lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, text, error, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits , cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, ((((ugly)))), (((duplicate))), ((morbid)), ((mutilated)), out of frame, extra fingers, mutated hands, ((poorly drawn hands)), (( poorly drawn face)), (((mutation))), (((deformed))), ((ugly)), blurry, ((bad anatomy)), (((bad proportions))), ((extra limbs )), cloned face, (((disfigured))), out of frame, ugly, extra limbs, (bad anatomy), gross proportions, (malformed limbs), ((missing arms)), ((missing legs)), (((extra arms))), (((extra legs))), mutated hands, (fused fingers), (too many fingers), (((long neck)))

items.name: Yoga Puss
items.description:
This one vector embedding will help you generate pictures of anime girls in tight yoga pants, viewed from behind.

The model used for the generation of these images was Anything 4.5. Anime models with danbooru style tags are the recommended use case for this embedding, as this embedding doesn't bring out the "puss" in other types of models. You should still get well figured women in tight yoga pants though.

Check out the images for the prompting information.

modelVersions.description:
This embedding was merged from two custom embeddings that were trained on five images each- one on five images at 512x512 of real live women(they exist!) in the desired pose, and another on five 512x768 images of anime girls in the same pose, that were created with the help of the first embedding. They were then merged to make this far superior embedding.

The first embedding was trained on SD 1.4, and the second on Anything 3.0. Merging was done with the Embedding Inspector extension for Automatic1111 Webui.

items.name: Vivid Watercolors
items.description:
Introducing my new Vivid Watercolors dreambooth model.

The model is trained with beautiful, artist-agnostic watercolor images using the midjourney method.

The token is "wtrcolor style"

It can be challenging to use, but with the right prompts, but it can create stunning artwork.

See an example prompt that I use in tests:

wtrcolor style, Digital art of (subject), official art, frontal, smiling, masterpiece, Beautiful, ((watercolor)), face paint, paint splatter, intricate details. Highly detailed, detailed eyes, [dripping:0.5], Trending on artstation by [artist]

Using "watercolor" in the pronpt is necessary to get a good watercolor texture, try words like face (paint, paint splatter, dripping).

items.name: My Hero Academia (Horikoshi Kouhei) Style LoRA
items.description:
Horikoshi Kouhei (My Hero Academia) Style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

This turned out better than expected and can do sfw and nsfw stuff. When I saw the baseball cap girl benchmark I was actually impressed.
I haven't tried it on other models beside Anything V4.5, as the results are stunning, but It can probably work just as fine in AbyssOrange and other nai based models with CLIP 2. I managed to replicate the style, which was the original intention, but also part of the main cast. Weight is safe to be set at around 0.5 and activates with horikoshi kouhei plus, if you want, character names and descriptions (e.g: bakugou katsuki, boku no hero academia).
Keep in mind this isn't really intended to copy heroaca characters, it just happens that it can do it. This is mostly intended to imitate Horikoshi's style.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Game Characters
items.description:
Welcome to my new model page dedicated to the characters from various video games.

Each version will represent a different character from the game, rather than an improvement to the model itself.

I have some ideas regarding future creations, but if you have your propositions - feel free to leave them in the comments and I might make that character! :-)

The base model is a mix of various models that were available in late November (Hassan 1.4 for sure, do not remember others) so the base quality is above pure 1.5.

Currently available:

  • Street Fighter - Chun-Li

  • Witcher 3 - Cirilla Fiona Elen Riannon

  • Cyberpunk 2077 - Female V

modelVersions.name: Witcher 3 - Cirilla Fiona Elen Riannon
modelVersions.description: I am aware that the previous Ciri model exists on Civitai (https://civitai.com/models/12/ciri-from-the-witcher) but I've tested that one and compared it to mine. That old model is overtrained and it is very hard to do something else than what it was trained for, while mine is not only more flexible but also seems to have better quality outputs.

modelVersions.name: Cyberpunk 2077 - Female V
modelVersions.description:
This model is quite personal since it is my character of V from Cyberpunk 2077.

This model was done as a case study to see if this idea is viable and it proved to be a total success. I spent with that character around 150 hours and now she comes to life!

NOTE: This is also a nice technique to create consistent characters if you wish to make some comics/graphics/illustrations - just create a character in the game (or some META character) and dreambooth it! As you can see in the examples - it can turn out quite marvelous.

modelVersions.name: Street Fighter - Chun-Li
modelVersions.description:
This model was trained on the same day as the TI version from @LucyFanboy ( https://civitai.com/models/5542 ) so I wasn't even sure if I should post it but after the discussion, the decision was made.

You can use this model on its own, you can even combine it with the TI for more interesting results!

And you can even merge it with other models (there is an example from samdoesart merge).

You can do anime, cartoons, renders, photorealistic, paintings, etc - whatever you wish :)

As per usual, the training data is included so if you feel like this does not need to be a checkpoint, you can train Lora, IT, or whatever you feel like :)

Since the limit was 20, here are the rest test images that I've made: https://imgur.com/a/JyntIA2

items.name: WLOP Style LoRA
items.description:
WLOP style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕


There is already a model checkpoint for wlop that you should definitely check out. However LoRA's are becoming the new way to basically mix models on the go and add artstyle and characters also combining multiple ones with many different pre-existing models. Wlop style is already used a lot in prompts, especially on Midjourney, so I made this.

For the preview pics I used AnyLoRA and Abyss Orange Mix V2 and a weight of 1 for the offset version (0.6 for the old one). Trigger word is of course wlop. Works well with DreamShaper too but you won't get the perfect style on it (it's trained on anime models). I also used CLIP skip 2.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Clarity
items.description:
Please Read Description

Important: Having multiple models uploaded here on civitai has made it difficult for me to respond to each and every comment. One of the ways I plan on addressing this is via the creation of a pdf guide for each and every model (think of it as the models documentation). This will take a while though. So in the meantime, if you have any questions or feedback -

visit my thread of the Unstable Diffusion Discord

Changelog:

8-20-23 v3 inpainting

  • Uploaded inpainting version of Clarity v3.

8-16-23 v3

  • Rebuilt from the ground-up using a fine-tuned base model, made specifically for Clarity.

  • More realistic skin texture.

  • Slightly sharper contrast.

  • Continued improvements on fabric details (next up armor 😉).

  • Improved lighting/shading.

  • Improvements to the autoencoders prompt adherence.

  • Note : Slightly different prompt design from v2, can use more natural language now.

Like photorealism? Try my new fine-tune 'Lomostyle'

How about art? Try my new fine-tune 'Doomer-Boomer'

VAE NOT REQUIRED BUT RECOMENDED

VAE is recommended - https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/sd-vae-ft-mse-original/tree/main

File Structure for AUTOMATIC1111-webui :

|──sd

|____|──stable-diffusion-webui

|____|____|──models

|____|____|____|──VAE

|____|____|____|____|──<Put your VAE file here>

Note: Description is slightly outdated. Reworking of the description coming soon with the release of Clarity v3.

Merged Models

A list of merged models can be found bellow in the description of the attached model version.

Capabilities

  • NSFW Photography

    • SFW Photography is also possible, see "Trigger Words" bellow.

  • Photorealistic 3D renders

  • Emphasis on human anatomy

Trigger Words

This checkpoint does not contain any trigger words.

However, placing some tags at the beginning of the prompts can heavily influence the generation.

These tags include:

"nsfw", "sfw", "erotica", and "nudity" | "3d render", "cartoon"

Note: For SFW generation, try adding sfw to your prompt and nsfw to your negative prompt. For NSFW generation, try adding either nsfw, erotica, or nudity to your prompt and sfw to your negative prompt. In general, this is more useful for generating sfw images. This concept also applies to 3rd render and cartoon. I recommend leaving 3rd render and cartoon both in your negative prompt for generating photographic images.

Basic Prompt Guide

This model heavily revolves around UnstablePhotorealv.5. This means that you can the tagging system for PhotoReal, although I would recommend using a combination of the PhotoReal comma system and more natural language prompting.

Guide to prompting with PhotoReal - https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-DDIHVbsYfynTp_rsKLu4b2tSQgxtO5F6pNsNla12k0/edit#heading=h.3znysh7

Example prompt using commas and natural language:

Positive

A Professional Full Body Photo, of a beautiful young woman, clothed, standing indoors, Caucasian, toned physique, strawberry red hair, neutral expression

Negative

I recommend something simple like, deformed, bad anatomy, disfigured, missing limb, floating limbs, twisted, blurry, fused fingers, long neck, words, logo, text, mutated hands, mutated fingers

Modify as needed. For example, adding 3d render, cartoon to your negative prompt will help generate photographic images.

The prompts for this model are fairly flexible, experiment to find out what works best for you.

items.description:
Eiichirou Oda (One Piece) style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

LoRA net for the style of my favourite mangaka. Oda's style has changed a lot during the years, so it was hard to capture his character design. This model mostly got his way of drawing lines and his coloring, plus certain details. It didn't really grasp character concept completely as much as my previous LoRA's (probably because the dataset was full of pics with multiple characters, as Oda mostly makes those), but it's pretty good when combined with embeddings (like the first Nico Robin pic, which is using my embedding, and unlike the second one, which is not using embeddings and looks like a mix between Nami and Robin).

Trigger word is oda eiichirou, suggested weight around 0.5 or 0.6 depending on the base model (I used Anything V4.5 here).

For the One Piece anime style please use this other LoRA I made: https://civitai.com/models/4219/one-piece-wano-style-lora

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Frottage - patterns and abstraction
items.description: "Frottage" is an artistic technique, consisting of placing some paper over any rough surface then rubbing it with pencils or pastels, to recreate the impression of its texture. For some reason the default model when asked to does not generate a meaningful effect. A large number of interesting effects can be achieved - blending from surreal to pure abstraction.

items.name: Maestro Evgeny Ponasenkov
items.description:
About model

the model was trained on the collected photos of Eugene's face from Instagram and Yandex images. It was important to find images without covering the face with anything, as well as with high-quality facial detail.

There were few suitable examples, so I had to manually upscale using the Codeformer and GFPGAN neural networks.

After that, I adjusted the saturation, white balance and brightness to one level among all the samples, of which there were 25 samples.

I created a model for a true aesthetes!

How to use

It is recommended to write the following tokens: evgeny-ponasenkov, greece, vegetation, intricate, sharp focus, official jacket, dslr, dark, sunglasses, 18's century, detailed.

Copy the prompt and parameters from the preview to this model — you will not lose.

Which model works best with

It is best to use the Deliberate_v2 model, but you can combine this LoRA with other solutions focused on photorealism, model will work perfectly with them.

Links and resources

You will find help in my telegram chat.
My Telegram channel.
